<?php
/**
 * SVG icon library — one source of truth for every inline icon in the theme.
 * -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 * Why inline SVG (not an icon font): crisper, recolours with `currentColor`,
 * no extra HTTP request, no FOUT, accessible. Why ONE map (not per-feature
 * helpers): so the header, the off-canvas menu, the prev/next arrows, the
 * social row, dark-mode — everything — pulls from the same place and we never
 * ship two slightly-different search icons.
 *
 * Two public functions:
 *   mike_icon( $name, $attrs )        → echo one icon by name (UI or brand).
 *   mike_social_icon( $url, $attrs )  → map a URL's domain → a brand icon.
 *
 * Icons are square 24×24 viewBox, stroke/fill tuned to look right at ~20–24px,
 * and inherit colour via `currentColor`. Paths are stored WITHOUT the outer
 * <svg> wrapper — mike_icon() builds the wrapper so sizing/aria/class are
 * applied in one consistent place.
 *
 * UI icons use stroke (line style, matches a clean editorial header); brand
 * icons use fill (recognisable logo silhouettes). Each entry declares which.
 */

if ( ! defined( 'ABSPATH' ) ) {
	exit;
}

